\begin_layout Subsection
General Description
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The ITWOM is a mathicmatical model that attempts to perdict how radio waves
 will propigate over known terrain features.
 This is useful for 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

link budgeting
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

, where communications technicians and radio operators attempt to map how
 well a radio link or broadcast will work over a given path or area.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
There is an existing implementation of the ITOWM.
 However, this implementation for a single, general-purpose CPU.
 I believe it may be possible to achieve a significant increase in performance
 by adapting the ITOWM to run in parallel on a GPGPU.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
The ITOWM and the Longely-Rice Model
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The ITOWM is largely derrived from the older Longely-Rice Model, with a
 number of changes and corrections that its author, Sidney E.
 Shumate, claims improve its overall accuracy.
 Addationally, their changes allow the practical use of higher-resoluation
 elevation data.
 Shumate also designed his code to work as a drop-in replacement for the
 Longely-Rice Model.
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "VTC_IWOTM"

\end_inset

 Since the two algorithims are so similar in terms of their overall structure
 and control flow, exiting research into how one is paraellized might be
 directly applicable to the other.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
SPLAT!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
SPLAT is a command-line wrapper program for the ITOWM, Longely-Rice Model
 and other RF-Propigation algorithims.
 It takes in appropiately formated elevation data and various prarmaters
 about each of the transmitters or receivers that the user wishes to model.
 It has the option of outputting a bitmap or a KML file for Google Earth
 for graphically representating coverage information.
 It also generates text files that contain information about each radio
 site and nearby obstructions.
 
