\begin_layout Section
Existing Related Works
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
There are a number the existing serial implementations of the Longley-Rice
 Model, including a refrence implementation maintained by the US Department
 of Commerce
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "us_commerce"

\end_inset

.
 This refrence implementation is the basis of the IWOTM
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "VTC_IWOTM"

\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Addationally, a pair of University of Arizona researchers have recently
 made implementations of the Longley-Rice Model for both for IBM's Cell
 proscessor and for Nvidia's Tesla C870 GPU
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "lrp_itm_gpu"

\end_inset

.
 These reaserchers foudn that were able to reduce execuation times to less
 than a second.
 They also found that the Telsa GPU was around 2-3 times as fast as the
 IBM cell proscessor.
 This confirms that the Longely-Rice Model is suitable for paraell proscesing,
 which makes it highly likely that the IWOTM will have similar preformance
 gains when it is adapted for use on the GPU.
\end_layout

